The paper deals with analyzing real-time multimedia content from network cameras, which involves significant amounts of computing resources. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category. Additionally, the paper mentions analyzing images and videos, which are common tasks in Computer Vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of GPUs to accelerate analysis programs, which is a topic in Multimedia (cs.MM) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper describes a resource manager that solves a problem related to resource allocation, which could fall under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category.
